  "meetings.intro_title": "Decisions and actions never get lost",
  "meetings.intro_body": "Schedule project meetings, capture minutes and turn discussion into tracked action items with an owner and a due date. Set up a recurring series for standing site or coordination meetings, or import a summary from an existing write-up, so every decision and follow-up stays attached to the project record.",
  "meetings.intro_more": "Press **New Meeting**, choose a type (progress, design, safety, subcontractor, kickoff or closeout), set the date and time, location, chairperson and attendees, and capture the minutes. You can drop attachments onto the meeting. When the meeting has happened, mark it complete, and export a clean minutes PDF at any time. For standing meetings, set up a recurring series so the whole run is scheduled at once.\n\nYou can also import a meeting summary: upload a transcript from Teams, Google Meet, Zoom or Webex, and AI extracts the attendees, key topics, action items and decisions for you to review and edit before the meeting is created. Discussion turns into tracked action items that flow into Tasks with an owner and due date.\n\n**Getting the most out of it:**\n- Import a recording transcript to skip retyping minutes and capture action items automatically.\n- Review every extracted action and attendee before saving, since AI suggests and you confirm.",
    "moc.subtitle": "Capture, assess, and route deviations from the agreed design, scope, or process",
    "moc.title": "Management of Change",
    "moc.page_title": "Management of Change",
  "moc.intro_title": "Control changes before anyone acts",
  "moc.intro_body": "Capture a proposed deviation from the agreed design, scope or process, assess its cost, schedule, safety and quality impact, then route it through review and approval before work changes. Approved changes flow on to Variations and Change Orders so the commercial trail stays connected and every decision is kept for the audit record.",
  "moc.intro_more": "Press **New change request**, pick a category (engineering, scope, design, process, material, safety and more) and a risk level, name the change, describe what is changing and why, and record the headline cost and schedule impact. The request enters a controlled flow: Proposed, then Review, then Accept or Decline, then Implement. The page only offers the transitions that are legal for the current state, and each one captures a note for the audit trail.\n\nYou can add detailed impact assessment lines per area (cost, schedule, safety, quality, environment) with severity and mitigation. Approved changes carry on to Variations and Change Orders, and the row shows those links once they exist, so the commercial trail stays connected to every quality decision and dated step.\n\n**Getting the most out of it:**\n- Capture the cost and schedule delta up front so reviewers approve on real numbers.\n- Add a note on each transition, since the proposed, reviewed, decided and implemented dates become your audit record.",
    "ncr.subtitle": "Document non-conforming work, root causes, and corrective actions",
    "ncr.action_close": "Close NCR",
