  "ncr.intro_title": "Catch defective work, fix the cause",
  "ncr.intro_body": "Document work that does not meet specification (material, workmanship, design, documentation or safety), record the root cause and the corrective and preventive actions. NCRs are often raised straight from a failed Inspection, and when a defect carries a cost impact you can escalate it to a Change Order so the money and the quality trail stay connected.",
  "ncr.intro_more": "Press **New NCR**, pick the non-conformance type (material, workmanship, design, documentation or safety) and severity, then describe the defect, the location, and the root cause if known. The report moves through Identified, Under Review, Corrective Action, Verification and Closed. Expand a row to read the description, root cause, and the corrective and preventive actions, then press **Close NCR** when the issue is resolved.\n\nMany NCRs are raised straight from a failed Inspection, which pre-fills the report and tags its origin (a clash or a validation failure also tags the source). When an NCR carries a cost impact you can escalate it to a Change Order so the money and the quality trail stay connected. Cross-links jump to the source Inspection, Change Orders and the Punch List.\n\n**Getting the most out of it:**\n- Raise NCRs from the failed inspection rather than from scratch so they arrive pre-filled and traceable.\n- Record the root cause and preventive action, not just the fix, so the same defect does not recur.",
