  "rfi.intro_title": "Get a clear answer on the record",
  "rfi.intro_body": "Raise a question to the design team, set who owns the next move and a response due date, then track it from Open to Answered to Closed with a ball-in-court badge and an overdue counter. Attach the drawings in question from Documents, and when an answer carries cost you can spin it straight into a Variation. Export the full RFI log for the contract file.",
  "rfi.intro_more": "Press **New RFI** and write the subject and question, set a priority, pick a discipline, name who holds the ball in court and an assignee, then add a response due date. You can attach the drawings in question, either ticking existing project documents or dropping a file straight into the dropzone to upload it. Each RFI opens from Open to Answered to Closed, and the row shows a ball-in-court badge plus a running days-open and overdue counter.\n\nWhen an answer carries cost, expand an answered or closed RFI and press **Create Variation** to push it into the commercial trail. Attachments are pulled from Documents, the ball-in-court person comes from your team, and answered RFIs feed Correspondence as a linked thread.\n\n**Getting the most out of it:**\n- Use the saved-view chips (Mine, Awaiting me, Overdue) to scan what is on your plate.\n- Set a realistic due date so the overdue pill flags stalls early.\n- Flag cost impact on the RFI so the Variation hand-off is one click later.",
