    "submittals.title_required": "Title is required",
  "submittals.intro_title": "No work installed without sign-off",
  "submittals.intro_body": "Log each shop drawing, product data sheet, sample or certificate and move it through Draft, Submitted, Under Review, then Approved or Revise-and-resubmit, with a due-date and days-in-court badge so nothing stalls. Link a submittal to the BOQ positions it covers so you can see which items have approved documentation before they go to site.",
  "submittals.intro_more": "Press **New Submittal**, give it a title and spec section, pick the type (shop drawing, product data, sample, mock-up, test report, certificate or warranty) and a date required. The submittal starts as Draft, then you Submit it for review. A reviewer opens it and records a decision: Approved, Approved as Noted, Revise and Resubmit, or Rejected, with comments. A Revise-and-resubmit sends it back so the submitter edits and resubmits as the next revision.\n\nThe row carries a days-in-court badge and a due-date countdown so nothing stalls. Where your project has a submittal approval route configured under Governance, a multi-step sign-off runs instead of the direct review. Submittals can link to the BOQ positions they cover, and supporting files live in Documents.\n\n**Getting the most out of it:**\n- Link each submittal to its BOQ positions so you can see what has approved documentation before it goes to site.\n- Watch the days-in-court badge to chase a slow reviewer.",
