  "correspondence.intro_title": "Your evidence trail when claims start",
  "correspondence.intro_body": "Keep a contemporaneous register of every formal letter, notice, email and memo exchanged with project parties. Log each entry, attach the source file and link it to the related Transmittals, RFIs, Documents and Contacts so a single thread of communication stays traceable end to end if a dispute arises. Inbound email auto-import is not wired yet, so entries are logged by hand today.",
  "correspondence.intro_more": "Press **New Letter** and the entry opens as outgoing by default. Set the direction, pick the type (letter, email, notice or memo), enter the From and To parties, set the sent and received dates, and add notes. Save it, then expand the row to attach the source file (PDF, image, Office document) and it is stored against the entry. You can edit or delete any entry later.\n\nEach entry can link to a related Transmittal, an RFI, and the project documents it refers to, so one communication thread stays traceable end to end if a dispute arises. Parties come from Contacts, attachments and links pull from Documents, Transmittals and RFIs. Inbound email and webhook auto-import are marked Coming Soon, so entries are logged by hand today.\n\n**Getting the most out of it:**\n- Log notices the day they are sent or received so the register stays contemporaneous.\n- Use the direction and type filters to pull a clean thread before a claim meeting.",
